libsigrokdecode
---------------
The bridge subprocess links libsigrokdecode at runtime and exposes its
protocol decoder set through WaveCrux. libsigrokdecode is part of the
SigRok project at <https://sigrok.org> and is licensed under the GNU
General Public License, version 3 or later.

The libsigrokdecode source and its protocol decoder corpus are
maintained by the SigRok project. WaveCrux is not affiliated with
SigRok and the use of "SigRok" in this project's name is purely
descriptive — it identifies the upstream protocol decoder ecosystem
this bridge integrates.

  Copyright (C) 2010-2025 The SigRok contributors


Python
------
The bridge subprocess embeds CPython at runtime to run the Python
protocol decoders shipped with libsigrokdecode. Python is distributed
under the Python Software Foundation License, Version 2 (PSF-2.0),
which is GPLv3-compatible.

  Copyright (c) 2001-2025 Python Software Foundation. All rights reserved.

The release archive on Windows ships the official Python embeddable
distribution from <https://python.org>. On Linux and macOS the bridge
links against the system or user-installed Python 3.10+.


